	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Melatite drops off CWG Clockwork Gnomebots models MA, MB, and MC.&nbsp;&nbsp;The drop frequency is rumored to be much better off MB and MC.  <br><br>I took on one MB and he used a 'Force Blowback' that was outrageously rude.  Luckily I had a wall behind me to stop against or it could've proved deadly.  Solusek's Eye has lava in many places and falling in can prove fatal unless you can TP or Gate all while taking guaranteed damage of about 40 points every tick.  Climbing out of the lava is just not possible in some locations and may require a GM /petition to get your corpse back.  All this combined with that 'Force Blowback' and you got one mean and nasty situation.  <br><br>Yes, killing gnomes and gnomebots will result in a loss of faction with the Ak'Anon gnomes.  About the only decent part about gathering the melatite will be looting the gnomes.  To put it bluntly, they are rich.  Seriously rich compared to anything on Antonica prior to level 35.  Looting 10pp worth of items and coin off each gnome (but not gnomebot) is probably not an exaggeration.<br><br>For those people that are willing to cough up some cash to buy the melatite, one possible source is the gnome merchant deep in the gnome territory.  Players that are looking to drop the 5 pound bricks will often sell them to the merchant.  One word of caution; bring loads of cash.  The gnomes are rather protective of this metal and, to an "apprehensive" paladin with 87 charisma, wanted roughly 125pp for each piece.<br><br>I spent well over 40 hours at the Solusek's Eye front entrance as well.  I was frustrated and angry to find out I had to get deep into the dungeon to find the monsters that dropped melatite.  Between all the goblins at the front entrance, the "lava pits of death" awaiting the careless traveler, and the faction loss for killing other members of a 'good' race, obtaining the melatite is perhaps as difficult as killing any sand giant.<br><br>Since the gnomes are fairly deep into Sol A, the solo paladin is required to run a "gauntlet of death" to simply get to them.  Melatite is not NO DROP, but the funny thing is, very few people take on the gnomes either so that buying it proves just as impossible as if it were NO DROP.  <br><br>I have spent dozens of hours in Sol A trying to auction to buy the melatite.  I didn't even get one response to my auctions.  Not one.  "/auction WTB melatite.  Paying well."  Is this the kind of auction that discourages people from asking "paying how well?"  Despite this open ended auction, I received zero responses.  Read my lips... zero... auctioning consistently for over 10 hours inside the Sol A zone...  zero responses.  <br><br>Ok.  So I try and go into Sol A and get the melatite on my own.  A dozen goblins (level 20-28)along the path, all of which agro on everyone (regardless of level), will beat back the solo paladin before he even gets to see a gnome.  I saw these goblins agro on a level 60 warrior.  True, they were nothing but a nuisance to him, but they did agro.  Kinda clues you in on the nature of the environment.<br><br>Out of sheer luck I wandered by a level 40 halfling warrior that was hunting the gnomes for experience.  I asked him if he had any melatite and he just happened to have 2 bricks.  I needed a total of 6 at the time and he promised to sell me any he looted.  More than 8 hours of online time later he managed to loot all the bricks I needed.  <br><br>Melatite: rare to very rare drop off gnomebots.<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
